# Omninuera
## Offer Letter — AI Intern (Draft)

Date: [Date]

Dear [Candidate Name],

We are pleased to offer you an internship with Omninuera for the position of **AI Intern**. This letter outlines the terms and conditions of the internship. Please review and, if acceptable, sign and return a copy.

Position and Duration
- Position: AI Intern.
- Duration: 3 months.
- Start Date: [Start Date] (placeholder; actual start date to be confirmed).

Stipend
- You will receive a stipend of INR 10,000 per month for the duration of the internship, payable in accordance with Omninuera’s payroll schedule.

Work Location and Remote Requirement
- Work location: Fully remote.
- Timezone: Work is expected to be performed in alignment with Bengaluru (India) timezone.
- Remote work requirement: You are required to have a reliable internet connection, an appropriate remote work environment, and any equipment necessary to perform your duties unless otherwise provided or agreed in writing by Omninuera.

Employment Type and Future Employment
- This arrangement is an internship and not employment. It is intended for learning and training and does not by itself constitute a guarantee of future employment with Omninuera.

Working Hours
- Working hours are flexible, but you are expected to be available and responsive during Bengaluru business hours (typically 10:00 AM — 6:00 PM IST) as reasonably required by your reporting manager.
- Exact weekly hours and schedule will be agreed upon with your Reporting Manager.

Reporting
- You will report to: [Reporting Manager].

Duties and Responsibilities
During the internship you will be expected to:
- Assist with machine learning model development and experimentation.
- Assist with data labeling, preprocessing, and dataset management.
- Run experiments and help evaluate model performance.
- Prepare and maintain technical documentation, experiment logs, and reports.
- Participate in team meetings and code reviews as requested.
- Perform other reasonably related tasks as assigned.

Confidentiality and Intellectual Property
- Confidentiality: During and after the internship, you must keep confidential all non-public information and trade secrets of Omninuera and its clients that you access or learn about. You must not disclose or use such information for any purpose other than performing your internship duties.
- IP Assignment: You agree that all inventions, designs, discoveries, work product, code, algorithms, documentation, and other materials (collectively, "Work Product") conceived, created, developed, or reduced to practice by you during the internship and within the scope of your duties (or using Omninuera resources) shall be the sole and exclusive property of Omninuera. You hereby assign to Omninuera all rights, title and interest in such Work Product and agree to execute any documents reasonably requested to confirm such assignment.

Background Verification
- This offer is conditional upon successful background verification and any other pre-internship checks required by Omninuera. Failure to clear background verification may result in the withdrawal of this offer.

Notice and Termination
- Termination for convenience: Either party may terminate this internship for any reason by providing at least one (1) week’s written notice.
- Omninuera reserves the right to terminate the internship immediately for cause, including breach of confidentiality, misconduct, or violation of company policies.

Internship Completion Certificate
- Upon satisfactory completion of the internship and fulfillment of assigned duties, Omninuera will issue an internship completion certificate stating the period of internship and a brief description of the work performed.

Company Policies and Code of Conduct
- Your internship will be subject to Omninuera’s standard policies and procedures, including but not limited to the Code of Conduct, IT and security policies, and anti-harassment policies. You are expected to comply with all applicable policies during your internship.

Data Security and Privacy
- You must follow Omninuera’s data security and privacy policies when handling any company or client data. Any use, transfer, or retention of data must comply strictly with those policies.

Acceptance
To accept this offer, please sign and date below and return a scanned copy of this letter. This offer is valid until [Offer Expiry Date] unless extended in writing.

Sincerely,

For Omninuera

_______________________________  
Name: [Authorized Representative]  
